{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb2c7e9c-beaa-42fc-b8d1-1519f787e126","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` bundles MSTest runner, framework, and assertions automatically.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings` or assembly attribute)\n\nAdd to your project root a file or simply use an assembly-level attribute. The simplest way — add a file like `Usings.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel by default.\n\n## 3. Sequential database tests\n\nDecorate your integration test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Should_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Should_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll methods in that class will run sequentially and won't overlap with other parallel tests.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:**\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| SDK | `MSTest.Sdk/3.7` (no extra PackageReferences needed) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential opt-out | `[DoNotParallelize]` on class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dd32f907-51ab-4381-8294-7af199bff4ac","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"E447:9D49C:3E9DD40:44CCFB7:6A02FC09"},"id":"9fa2364b-9f35-4a82-97d0-23562e1a23b0","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:08:24.238Z","parentId":"295e1cbf-e2f6-44f3-951c-fe9761c06684"}
